Ag-Grid is a powerful JavaScript library for building interactive, cross-platform data grids. To disable checkboxes conditionally, you can use a cell renderer function that checks the condition and applies the appropriate CSS properties to the checkbox.

Here's an example of how you can disable the checkboxes based on a specific condition:

1. First, you need to create a custom cell renderer for the checkbox. The renderer function is a callback that Ag-Grid calls whenever it needs to render a cell.
```javascript
function checkboxRenderer(params) {
    const { rowNode, colDEF, value, data } = params;
    const checkbox = document.createElement('input');
    checkbox.type = 'checkbox';
    checkbox.checked = value || data ? true : false;

    const span = document.createElement('span');
    span.className = 'ag-checkbox';
    span.appendChild(checkbox);

    const parentElement = React.useRef(null);
    ReactDOM.render(<div ref={parentElement} key={rowNode.id}>{span}</div>, null);
    const boundParentElement = parentElement.current;

    const disableCheckbox = () => {
        checkbox.disabled = true;
    };

    const enableCheckbox = () => {
        checkbox.disabled = false;
    };

    if (colDEF && colDEF. checkboxProp && colDEF.checkboxProp.headerCheckboxSelectItemFunc) {
        colDEF.checkboxProp.headerCheckboxSelectItemFunc({ disableCheckbox, enableCheckbox, rowNode, colDEF, data });
    }

    return { rowNode, colDEF, checkbox: { element: checkbox, bean: ReactDOM.findDOMNode(boundParentElement.parentNode) }};
}
```

